<FIGURE>
<PB REF="00000042.tif"></FIGURE>
<FIGURE>
<PB REF="00000043.tif"></FIGURE>

<PB REF="00000044.tif"></P>
<L>
<PB REF="00000045.tif" N="9">&amp; &thorn;e kinges baxtere iwreyed was ful stronge.</L>
<L>To Iosep hi be&thorn; icast, &amp; &thorn;er hi ligge&thorn; longe,</L>
<L N="250">&amp; in &thorn;e prison ligge&thorn; mid ful muchel wronge.</L>
<L>Nabbe&thorn; hi none blisse of harpe ne of songe,</L>
<L>Of olde ne of &yogh;unge, of fremede ne of sibbe,</L>
<L>Leuere hem were to be ded &thorn;en so longe to libbe.</L>
<L>Hit fel in one ni&yogh;te &thorn;e botiler feng to slepe,</L>
<L N="255">A swi&thorn;e muri sweuene him &thorn;u&yogh;te &thorn;at he gan mete,</L>
<L>&THORN;at in &thorn;e win&yogh;arde &thorn;e kinges coupe he ber,</L>
<L>&amp; wrong hit of &thorn;e grapes ful of win cler.</L>
<L>&THORN;e baxtere mette an o&thorn;er, nas hit nou&yogh;t so god,</L>
<L>In &thorn;e bachuse him &thorn;u&yogh;te &thorn;at he stod,</L>
<L>Of bred he fulde a basket &amp; to &thorn;e halle he wolde hit bere,</L>
<L N="261">&THORN;e foules bi &thorn;e lifte hit gonnen al totere.</L>
<L>Amorewen ase &thorn;ei seten wi&thorn; Iosep atte bord,</L>
<L>Here sweuen hi him tolden word after word.</L>
<L>Iosep here sweuen sone haue&thorn; arou&yogh;t.</L>
<L N="265">'&YOGH;e ssulen in &thorn;is &thorn;ridde dai of prison ben ibrou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&THORN;ou ssalt, sir baxtere, anhonged be ful heye,</L>
<L>Foules bi &thorn;e lifte holen out &thorn;in eye.</L>
<L>&THORN;ou ssalt, sire botiler, &thorn;i mester vnderfonge,</L>
<L>Wi&thorn; alle worssipe mest &thorn;e king serue longe.</L>
<L N="270">&amp; wen me serue&thorn; &thorn;e king mid harpe &amp; mid songe,</L>
<L>&THORN;ench on seli Iosep, &thorn;at her li&thorn; mid wronge.'<MILESTONE N="6a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Also ase Iosep seide, also hit bicam:</L>
<L>&THORN;e botiler of Iosep lute &yogh;eme nam,</L>
<L>&THORN;at in &thorn;e prison li&thorn; mid ful muche wronge.</L>
<L N="275">Na&thorn; he none blisse of harpe ne of songe,</L>
<L>Of olde ne of &yogh;unge, of fremede ne of sibbe,</L>
<L>Leuere him<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>hem.</I></NOTE> were to be ded &thorn;en so longe to libbe.
<PB REF="00000046.tif" N="10"></L>
<L>Wel ou&yogh;te we to heren<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>w&dotb;heren.</I></NOTE> him &thorn;at is ri&yogh;twis,</L>
<L>&amp; nou &yogh;e mowen ihere hou hende oure Louerd is,</L>
<L N="280">Hou feire he sende help to Iosep &thorn;e &yogh;ungling</L>
<L>&THORN;ur&yogh; a sweuene &thorn;at mette Pharaon &thorn;e king.</L>
<L>&THORN;e king ase he slepte him &thorn;u&yogh;te &thorn;at he rod</L>
<L>In a medewe grene &thorn;at long was &amp; brod.</L>
<L>Seue kuin fatte him &thorn;u&yogh;te &thorn;at he sau&yogh; gon:</L>
<L N="285">So fatte ne so feire sau&yogh; he neuere non.</L>
<L>O&thorn;er seue lene to&yogh;eines hem gonne gon</L>
<L>&amp; frete &thorn;e seue fatte kyn eueruchon.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e seue fatte kin alle forswolewed were,</L>
<L>&THORN;e seue kin lene neuere &thorn;e fullore nere.</L>
<L N="290">Amorewen &thorn;e king awoc, his sweuen he tolde</L>
<L>Vrles &amp; barons &amp; burgeis ful bolde.</L>
<L>Ac &thorn;er nas nei&thorn;er baron ne kni&yogh;t</L>
<L>&THORN;at of &thorn;isse &thorn;inge cou&thorn;e reden him aiwi&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&THORN;o herde &thorn;e botiler of &thorn;isse sweuene speke,</L>
<L N="295">&THORN;o &thorn;ou&yogh;te he furst on Iosep, &thorn;at so longe lai bisteke.</L>
<L>He cam to &thorn;e kinge &amp; tolde him anon</L>
<L>Of him &amp; of &thorn;e baxtere hou hit was igon.</L>
<L>'Louerd, of &thorn;i sweuene &yogh;if he ne sei&thorn; &thorn;en ende<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>&thorn;enende.</I></NOTE>,<MILESTONE N="6b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Do me, Louerd, a&yogh;ein into &thorn;ine bende.'</L>
<L N="300">&THORN;enne seide Faraon, Faraon &thorn;e king,</L>
<L>'Let bringe bifore me &thorn;ene &yogh;ungling.</L>
<L>&YOGH;if he of mi sweuene sei&thorn; me &thorn;en ende,</L>
<L>Al his gult ich him for&yogh;iue &amp; quite faten<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>faten</I> altered from <I>faren.</I></NOTE> of bende.'</L>
<L>For&thorn; me fecche&thorn; Iosep, &thorn;at bloc was &amp; lene,</L>
<L N="305">Durste for &thorn;e quene no man him bimene.</L>
<L>'Louerd,' seide Iosep, 'ich hit &thorn;onke &thorn;e,</L>
<L>Nou ich wot mid iwisse islawe &thorn;at ich ssal be,
<PB REF="00000047.tif" N="11"></L>
<L>Nou ich wot mid iwisse &thorn;at ich ssal ben islawe,</L>
<L>For nabbi none blisse of mi lifdawe.'</L>
<L N="310">Ac &thorn;e king wel feire his sweuen he tolde,</L>
<L>&amp; bad swi&thorn;e feire reden &thorn;at he hit ssolde.</L>
<L>'Louerd,' seide Iosep, '&thorn;i sweuen is e&thorn; to telle,</L>
<L>Oure Louerd wole in &thorn;i lond muche prude felle<NOTE PLACE="foot">MS. <I>falle.</I></NOTE>.</L>
<L>Ac &thorn;ou ssalt habbe ra&thorn;er seue &yogh;er blisse of alle gode</L>
<L N="315">&THORN;ur&yogh; a swete water ssal comen of Niles flode.</L>
<L>&THORN;ou ssalt haue &thorn;enne<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;enne</I>] MS. <I>&thorn;er.</I></NOTE> hunger &amp; hete,</L>
<L>Wone of alle gode, of drinken<NOTE PLACE="foot">The <I>k</I> altered from another letter.</NOTE> &amp; of mete.</L>
<L>&THORN;is is &thorn;i sweuene, sire king, &thorn;ench &thorn;ou &thorn;eron,</L>
<L>Bote Crist be &thorn;in help, Egipte is al agon.'</L>
<L N="320">Heron &thorn;e king &thorn;enche&thorn; bi ni&yogh;t &amp; bi dai,</L>
<L>Not he a liue what he do mai.</L>
<L>Heron &thorn;e king &thorn;enche&thorn; bi dai &amp; bi ni&yogh;t,</L>
<L>Me ne cou&thorn;e of &thorn;is &thorn;inge reden him no wi&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne spac an old man &thorn;at was wis of speche.<NOTE PLACE="foot">Between foll. 6 and 7 a leaf has been cut out.</NOTE></L>
<L>Wenne ich &thorn;enche on Abraham, hou he gan &thorn;ider wende:<MILESTONE N="7a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="326">Muche &thorn;o &thorn;olede Abraham ssame mid his wiue,</L>
<L>&amp; se&thorn;&thorn;en atte nende of lond me gan him driue.</L>
<L>&amp; wenne &thorn;e ri&yogh;twise man &thorn;olede such ssome,</L>
<L>Into Egipte to sende &thorn;unche&thorn; me no gome.</L>
<L N="330">Ofte of &thorn;is smal chaf &thorn;is bre&thorn;ren brou&yogh;ten hom,</L>
<L>&amp; for wone of mete maden muche mon.</L>
<L>Beniamin &thorn;e &yogh;unge bad his moder bred,</L>
<L>&amp; seide he was afingred &thorn;at he was nei&yogh; ded.</L>
<L>&THORN;e moder swor swi&thorn;e &thorn;at bred nadda non,</L>
<L N="335">&THORN;o wrong he his honden, Iacob &thorn;e elde man,</L>
<L>For leuere were Iacob of liue for to ben
<PB REF="00000048.tif" N="12"></L>
<L>&THORN;en bi Beniamin &thorn;e &yogh;unge &thorn;ese pines isen.</L>
<L>&YOGH;it Beniamin &thorn;e &yogh;unge make&thorn; muche mon</L>
<L>&THORN;enne clepede Iacob his sones eueruchon.</L>
<L N="340">'Sones,' seide Iacob, 'Nede &yogh;e mote wende</L>
<L>For to sech vs corn in &thorn;issen estende.</L>
<L>For betere &yogh;ou is to swinke &amp; erne &yogh;oure mete</L>
<L>&THORN;enne at hom to deye on hunger &amp; on hete.</L>
<L>Nime&thorn; &yogh;oure assen &amp; nime&thorn; &yogh;oure horn,</L>
<L N="345">Nime&thorn; &yogh;ou seluer &amp; gold to buggen vs corn.</L>
<L>Ac Beniamin &thorn;e &yogh;unge bileue ssal at hom;</L>
<L>Me rewe&thorn; euere Iosep &thorn;at afelde was igon.</L>
<L>For &yogh;if he hadde at hom bileued, &yogh;it he were aliue;</L>
<L>For &thorn;e loue of Iosep be ich neuere bli&thorn;e.</L>
<L N="350">Nime&thorn; &yogh;oure wepnen &amp; wende&thorn; &yogh;oure wai,</L>
<L>Berewe &yogh;ou from care oure Louerd, &thorn;at wel mai.'</L>
<L>Feire fare&thorn; &thorn;is &yogh;unge men bi dai &amp; bi ni&yogh;t<MILESTONE N="7b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Into Egipte lond &thorn;at hi comen ri&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Muche was &thorn;e blisse &amp; muche was &thorn;e gome</L>
<L N="355">In water &amp; in londe of wilde &amp; of tome.</L>
<L>Muche was &thorn;e blisse &thorn;at hi &thorn;ar iseye,</L>
<L>Bernes ful riche &amp; mowen ful heye.</L>
<L>Muche was &thorn;e blisse after here swinke</L>
<L>&THORN;at hi &thorn;are funden of mete &amp; of drinke.</L>
<L N="360">Hem oftok a menestral, his harpe he bar arugge.</L>
<L>'Whennes be &yogh;e, &yogh;unge men? Ich bidde &thorn;at &yogh;e me sigge.</L>
<L>Me &thorn;unche&thorn; bi &yogh;oure assen &thorn;at corn &yogh;e wolde begge,</L>
<L>&amp; ich &yogh;ou wole bringe to &thorn;e tubrugge.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&THORN;ar &thorn;e</I>] MS. <I>&thorn;arle.</I></NOTE> hendeste man &thorn;at euere is aliue</L>
<L N="365">&YOGH;ou wole gistni toni&yogh;t &amp; make &yogh;ou ful bli&thorn;e.</L>
<L>&YOGH;e &thorn;unche&thorn; ferrene men &amp; alle freboren,</L>
<L>Toni&yogh;t ssal mani kni&yogh;tchild knele &yogh;ou biforen.'
<PB REF="00000049.tif" N="13"></L>
<L>He brou&yogh;tem to &thorn;e castel ase he hem bihet,</L>
<L>&amp; spac wi&thorn; &thorn;e porter in &thorn;at he hem let.</L>
<L N="370">Hi seyen in &thorn;e castel mani riche &thorn;ing,</L>
<L>&amp; Iosep sitten in halle, such hit were a king.</L>
<L>Ac if hi wenden Iosep &thorn;er for to sen,</L>
<L>Leuere hem were alle at hom on hunger ded to ben.</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;ese ten bre&thorn;ren comen into &thorn;e halle,</L>
<L N="375">Tofore Ioseppes fet akne hi valle&thorn; alle.</L>
<L>'Arise&thorn; vp', seide Iosep, 'Sitte &yogh;e nou&yogh;t akne,</L>
<L>Ac telle&thorn; me wel feire wat &yogh;oure wille be.'</L>
<L>'From Ierusalem', quod Ruben, 'we be&thorn; hider icome,</L>
<L>Let sullen vs corn, louerd, for Godes loue<MILESTONE N="8a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="380">Old man is oure fader &amp; corn na&thorn; he non,</L>
<L>For muchel one nede we be&thorn; hider igon.'</L>
<L>&THORN;enne seide Iosep, such hit were his gome,</L>
<L>'Wat is', he seide, '&yogh;oure faderes nome?'</L>
<L>'Vre fader hei&yogh;te Iacob, vre moder Rachel.'</L>
<L N="385">Mid &thorn;at ilke worde he knew hem ful wel.</L>
<L>&THORN;o Iosep iherde &thorn;at his fader was aliue,</L>
<L>Nas neuere for his fader child also bli&thorn;e.</L>
<L>He go&thorn; into &thorn;e boure &amp; wepe&thorn; for blisse,</L>
<L>Sore he is alonged his bre&thorn;ren to kisse.</L>
<L N="390">Iosep cam into halle, &thorn;e water he lette bringe,</L>
<L>&amp; halde to here honden mid his wite vingres.</L>
<L>Feire be&thorn; &thorn;is &yogh;unge men iserued &thorn;ilke ni&yogh;t</L>
<L>Of mete ne of drinke trukede hem no wi&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Iosep ful riche win lette to him bringe,</L>
<L N="395">&amp; so he bad &thorn;is children on Ebrewisse singe.</L>
<L>&amp; so hi sungen alle ase Iosep hem bad,</L>
<L>Se&thorn;&thorn;e he cam into Egipte nas Iosep so glad.</L>
<L>Al of rede wete here assen he lette seme,</L>
<L>For to meten here corn nam he none &yogh;eme.
<PB REF="00000050.tif" N="14"></L>
<L N="400">Nou dude Iosep a swi&thorn;e wonder&thorn;ing,</L>
<L>He nam a guldene nap, was Pharaones &thorn;e king,</L>
<L>&amp; putte in &thorn;ones sakke wi&thorn;inne &thorn;e prene,</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;erof cam<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>cam</I>] MS. <I>come</I></NOTE> &thorn;is &yogh;unge men swi&thorn;e muche tene.</L>
<L>Feire hi nomen leue to wenden here way</L>
<L N="405">Toward here contre a lutel ere day.</L>
<L>Ase hi ferden here wai in &thorn;e morewentide,<MILESTONE N="8b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>&THORN;enne seyen hi twolf &yogh;unge men after hem ride</L>
<L>Mid helm &amp; mid brunie, mid swerdes outdrawe,</L>
<L>&THORN;o wenden &thorn;ese ten bre&thorn;ren alle to ben islawe.</L>
<L N="410">'Abide&thorn;', hi seiden, '&thorn;eues, abide&thorn;, &yogh;e be&thorn; inome,</L>
<L>Tofore &thorn;e stiward a&yogh;ein &yogh;e ssulen alle come</L>
<L>For a guldene nap &thorn;at &yogh;e habbe&thorn; inome.</L>
<L>&YOGH;if &yogh;e in &thorn;is londe mid &thorn;ef&thorn;e be&thorn; ifonge,</L>
<L>&YOGH;oure dom is idemed, alle &yogh;e wor&thorn;e&thorn; anhonge;</L>
<L N="415">For &yogh;oure assen isemed al of rede golde</L>
<L>Of Faraones lond &thorn;e king faren &yogh;e ne ssolde.'</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;ese ten bre&thorn;ren turne&thorn; hem a&yogh;ein</L>
<L>Mid reu&thorn;fule wepe &amp; mid dreri drem,</L>
<L>Tofore &thorn;e stiward a&yogh;ein hi be&thorn; alle ibrou&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="420">&THORN;e nap in here sakke sone hit is isou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&THORN;e nap is ifunde sone &amp; anon,</L>
<L>Nou wringe&thorn; hi here honden &thorn;is bre&thorn;ren eueruchon.</L>
<L>Iosep sau&yogh; his bre&thorn;ren wepe, sore hit him gan rewe,</L>
<L>He nolde in none wise &yogh;it &thorn;at hi him knewe.</L>
<L N="425">Iosep feng &thorn;ene nap, mid pal he was biweued,</L>
<L>He lokede on his bre&thorn;ren, &amp; ssok on hem his heued.</L>
<L>Awaried wor&thorn;e swikedom &amp; &thorn;at hit erest funde,</L>
<L>So mani gultelese man hit bringe&thorn; to &thorn;e grunde.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne seide Iosep to his bre&thorn;ren anon,
<PB REF="00000051.tif" N="15"></L>
<L N="430">'Habbe &yogh;e', he seide, 'mo bre&thorn;ren at hom?'</L>
<L>'&YOGH;e, louerd', seide Ruben, 'a child &thorn;er is at hom</L>
<L>For to gladen oure fader, &thorn;at make&thorn; muche mon</L>
<L>For a sone &thorn;at he les &amp; louede so his lif,<MILESTONE N="9a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Ne mi&yogh;te him se&thorn;&thorn;e gladien his child no his wif.'</L>
<L N="435">Hi swore bi &thorn;ilke louerd &thorn;at is hei&yogh; in heuene,</L>
<L>'More he louede &thorn;ane sone &thorn;an vs alle elleuene.</L>
<L>&THORN;enne seide Iosep, 'Wolle &yogh;e me ihere,</L>
<L>&YOGH;if &yogh;e of Egi&thorn;te lond wolle&thorn; faren skere,</L>
<L>Ich &yogh;ou wolle tellen one tidinge,</L>
<L N="440">&YOGH;e ssule make me siker &thorn;at ilke child me bringe.'</L>
<L>'Louerd,' seide Ruben, 'we ssule ful fain</L>
<L>Beniamin &thorn;e bringen &amp; alle comen a&yogh;ein</L>
<L>&amp; &thorn;i dom &thorn;olie when we be&thorn; icome,</L>
<L>Habbe we &thorn;e blessinge of oure fader inome.'</L>
<L N="445">Iosep dranc to Ruben mid ful riche win,</L>
<L>&amp; alle hi pli&yogh;ten trou&thorn;e to bringe Beniamin.</L>
<L>Feire fare&thorn; &thorn;is &yogh;unge men bi dai &amp; bi ni&yogh;t</L>
<L>To here fader Iacob &thorn;at hi comen ri&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&amp; habbe&thorn; to Iacob al &thorn;is corn ibrou&yogh;t:</L>
<L N="450">Nou ha&thorn; Beniamin inou&yogh; &thorn;at eror he ha&thorn; bisou&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Iacob of &thorn;is corn was swi&thorn;e glad:</L>
<L>Nou ha&thorn; Beniamin inou&yogh; &thorn;at he er bad.</L>
<L>Iacob of &thorn;is corn aboute sende anon</L>
<L>To frendes &thorn;at for hunger maden muche mon.</L>
<L N="455">Ac alle &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>&thorn;is</I>] MS. <I>hise.</I> Cp. note.</NOTE> ten bre&thorn;ren to fote &thorn;ei be&thorn; ifalle,</L>
<L>&THORN;e trou&thorn;e &thorn;at hi pli&yogh;ten hi him telle&thorn; alle.</L>
<L>&THORN;o Iacob iherde &thorn;is sori tidinge,</L>
<L>Adoun he fel iswowe, his honden he gan wringe.</L>
<L>'A! wher artou, mi de&thorn;, whi neltou me fonge?</L>
<L N="460">Nou mi wrecchede lif ilast al to longe.<MILESTONE N="9b" UNIT="folio">
<PB REF="00000052.tif" N="16"></L>
<L>Iloren ich haue Iosep, &thorn;at ich louede so swi&thorn;e,</L>
<L>&amp; nou ich ssal Beniamin, be ich neuere bli&thorn;e.</L>
<L>Ac nellich nou&yogh;t, mine sones, &yogh;oure trou&thorn;e &thorn;at &yogh;e breke,</L>
<L>Oure Louerd, wen his wille is, wel he me mai awreke.'</L>
<L N="465">&THORN;is bre&thorn;ren nime&thorn; Beniamin &amp; for&thorn; hi hine lede&thorn;,</L>
<L>Iacob falle&thorn; iswowe &amp; for serewe grede&thorn;.</L>
<L>Feire fare&thorn; &thorn;is &yogh;unge men bi dai &amp; bi ni&yogh;t</L>
<L>Into Egipte lond &thorn;at hi comen ri&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Hi comen into &thorn;e castel &thorn;er Iosep was in,</L>
<L N="470">Ruben him biteche&thorn; his bro&thorn;er Beniamin.</L>
<L>&THORN;o Iosep isau&yogh; his bre&thorn;ren alle elleuene,</L>
<L>Him &thorn;u&yogh;te &thorn;at he was bli&thorn;ore &thorn;en &thorn;au&yogh; he were in heuene.</L>
<L>He go&thorn; into &thorn;e boure &amp; wepe&thorn; for blisse,</L>
<L>Sore he is alonged his bre&thorn;ren to kisse.</L>
<L N="475">'Louerd,' seide Iosep, 'ich hit &thorn;onke &thorn;e,</L>
<L>Nou &thorn;e eleue sterren icomen be&thorn; to me.</L>
<L>Mi fader &amp; mi moder haddich iwonne,</L>
<L>&THORN;enne hadde ich iwis &thorn;e mone &amp; &thorn;e sunne.</L>
<L>Feire be&thorn; &thorn;is &yogh;unge men iserued &thorn;ilke ni&yogh;t,</L>
<L N="480">Of mete ne of drinke trukede hem no wi&yogh;t.</L>
<L>Iosep cam to &thorn;e bord, anon he hem tolde</L>
<L>'Ich am,' he seide, 'Iosep, into Egipte &thorn;at &yogh;e solde.'</L>
<L>&amp; so he ge&thorn; to boure ri&yogh;t from &thorn;e bord,</L>
<L>&amp; wepe&thorn; for blisse &thorn;at he ne mai speken a word.</L>
<L N="485">&THORN;enne seide Ruben, 'Ne seidich &yogh;ou inou&yogh;,</L>
<L>To sungen on &thorn;at child &thorn;at &yogh;e hadden wou&yogh;.</L>
<L>Nolde &yogh;e me ileue &yogh;oure neuer on,<MILESTONE N="10a" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L>Nou is icome &thorn;e time &thorn;at we be&thorn; alle agon.'</L>
<L>Iosep cam into halle &amp; sau&yogh; his bre&thorn;ren wepe,</L>
<L N="490">He kisse&thorn; Beniamin anon, his neb he gan wipe,</L>
<L>&amp; so he go&thorn; bi rewe &amp; kusse&thorn; hem eueruchon,</L>
<L>Se&thorn;&thorn;e he cam into Egypte nas he so bli&thorn;e man.
<PB REF="00000053.tif" N="17"></L>
<L>&THORN;enne seide Iosep to his bre&thorn;ren anon,</L>
<L>'&THORN;e sweuene &thorn;at me mette, &yogh;it nis hit nou&yogh;t agon.</L>
<L N="495">Ac ase &yogh;e wolle&thorn;, bre&thorn;ren, &thorn;at ich be aliue,</L>
<L>&YOGH;e ssule fecchen oure fader &amp; maken him ful bli&thorn;e,</L>
<L>&amp; oure kun alle &amp; oure nextfolde,</L>
<L>&THORN;at ich mowe in &thorn;is lond here lif holde.</L>
<L>For &thorn;e hunger ha&thorn; ibe two &yogh;er swi&thorn;e strong,</L>
<L N="500">&amp; &yogh;it hit laste&thorn; fiue, &amp; &thorn;at is al to long.'</L>
<L>Feire he ssrudde his bre&thorn;ren mid derewor&thorn;e clo&thorn;,</L>
<L>His bre&thorn;ren &thorn;at ride&thorn; &amp; here men &thorn;at go&thorn;.</L>
<L>Of fiss &amp; of flesse, of foules ibake,</L>
<L>He lette senden in cartes to his fader sake,</L>
<L N="505">Clo&thorn;es of skarlet &amp; of sabelin,</L>
<L>Of honi &amp; of corn, of fruit &amp; of win,</L>
<L>Nappes of seluer &amp; ringes of golde,</L>
<L>&amp; alle prudene mest &thorn;at hi leden wolde.</L>
<L>Feire fare&thorn; &thorn;is &yogh;unge men bi dai &amp; bi ni&yogh;t</L>
<L N="510">To here fader Iacob &thorn;at hi comen ri&yogh;t.</L>
<L>&amp; habbe&thorn; to Iacob ibrou&yogh;t al &thorn;is &thorn;ing,</L>
<L>&amp; segge&thorn; &thorn;at Iosep is in Egipte ase hei&yogh; as a king.</L>
<L>&THORN;o Iacob iherde &thorn;at Iosep was aliue,</L>
<L>Nas neuere for his child fader so bli&thorn;e.<MILESTONE N="10b" UNIT="folio"></L>
<L N="515">He caste awei his crucche, his mantel he feng,</L>
<L>Feire he platte his her wi&thorn; a selkene streng.</L>
<L>He toc his benetene hat wi&thorn; pal &thorn;at was biweued.</L>
<L>'Of sor &amp; of serewe nou ich am bireued,</L>
<L>For nou me &thorn;unche&thorn; &thorn;at ich mai flen as an ern</L>
<L N="520">For &thorn;e loue of Iosep, mi leueste bern.'</L>
<L>Iacob rod singinde, such hit were a child,</L>
<L>'For &thorn;e loue of Iosep nou ich am &yogh;ung &amp; wild.'</L>
<L>&THORN;o Iosep iherde of his fader come,</L>
<L>Kni&yogh;tes inowe mid him he ha&thorn; inome,
<PB REF="00000054.tif" N="18"></L>
<L N="525">Mid harpe &amp; mid pipe, mid ioie &amp; mid songe</L>
<L>Mid alle worssipe mest his fader to vnderfonge.</L>
<L>Ich &yogh;ou mai telle &amp; ich &yogh;ou mai singe</L>
<L>&THORN;at bli&thorn;e was Pharaon of Ioseppes &thorn;inge.</L>
<L>&amp; lond swi&thorn;e riche bi &thorn;e seeside</L>
<L N="530">He ha&thorn; to Iacob i&yogh;iue &amp; castles heye &amp; wide.</L>
<L>Nou haue&thorn; Iacob wele &amp; alle winne</L>
<L>Mid his sones twolue &amp; mid his o&thorn;er kunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;e blisse is ful swete &thorn;at come&thorn; after wo,</L>
<L>Wel is him a liue &thorn;at his care mot atgo.</L>
<L N="535">Nou &thorn;unche&thorn; Iacob his lif swi&thorn;e swete</L>
<L>Of Iacob to telle nou ich mot nede lete.</L>
<L>Come neuere to &thorn;is hous worse tidinge</L>
<L>Bote alle worssipe mest &amp; Cristes blessinge. Amen.<NOTE PLACE="foot">After <I>Iosep</I> an <I>h</I> has been erased.</NOTE></L>
<TRAILER>Explicit Iacob &amp; Iosep.</TRAILER>
